This is my favorite bar in New York for a myriad of reasons, but I specifically return over and over again for the unmatched service I've encountered there. The bartenders are knowledgable, kind, and efficient, and the environment is charmingly old-world without tipping over into kitsch - "authentic", as the kids might say. I can't speak highly enough of the cocktails - fresh, well-balanced, and elegant. Perfect for a first date or a fifth date or solo outing or a quick drink with an old friend. Those of you who do not require that every recreational outing resemble the first hour of Disney's Wall-E will not be personally insulted that Brooklyn Social is cash only. There's an ATM in the back. You'll survive.
It’s definitely not a happening neighborhood if your looking for the latest and greatest however, this is the best your going to get in this area. Very yummy cocktails and a small cool vibe.

Normally I would give bk social a 5 star, but one bad experience has made me leave a review. I've been here so many times and always enjoyed it, old school cocktail joint, perfect place to get drinks with friends. But this time it was not enjoyable because the drinks were not good. And for $12 a cocktail they should be amazing. We ordered off the menu but classics drinks that are straightforward and simple to make. Not sure how you can mess up a dirty martini and make three of them all taste completely different! Also the bartender had a little bit of an attitude when given preference direction. Never should a proprietor make a customer feel like they're wrong especially when they're right!
